
    IT is all stsyetems go for the 3rd Annual INKasi Xperience taking place on the 16th of December at KwaMashu Freedom Park in KwaMashu, Durban. This year’s edition features top South African artists such as Distruction Boyz, Babes Wodumo, award winning Big Nuz, Dladla Mshunqisi, Zakwe, Zola 7, WTF, DJ Sox, DJ Happy Girl, Gagasi FM’s DJ LeSoul, DJ Vumar and DJ Sonic as well as many more. The show will be hosted by Gagasi FM personalities Felix Hlophe, Mzokoloko and Zola ZeeLovin, as well as Tha Simelani from Ukhozi FM.INKasi Xperience celebrates the ekasi offering of the three big townships within the Durban’s INK zone, which are Inanda, Ntuzuma and KwaMashu. “This is one event that reflects on the experiential offering of the INK townships, even with the line-up, you will see that its either artists with links to these townships or its artists that people from these townships can identify with,” says Kaslam Events Director Philani Ngwenya.Philani also emphasized that although the INKasi Xperience is being hosted in KwaMashu and is the celebration of the township experience, the event is not only aime at people from Inanda, Ntuzuma and Kwamashu, but it is for everyone who can relate to its positioning and offering. “We are inviting people from all corners of the Province and those that will be visiting from other Provinces for December holidays to come and celebrate Durban’s township experience. This is also a good opportunity to explore other parts of Durban because most of the times when you talk of the township experience in Durban, people think of one or two places. The event is outdoor, picnic style where people can bring in their food baskets, coolers and camp chairs, and enjoy performances by various artists live on stage,” adding Ngwenya.Tickets are available at Computickets at R100 for general access and R200 for VIP, they will also be available at the door. Entry with a cooler box will cost R100 however there are no bottles allowed, food and drinks will also be sold inside the venue. The event will start at 14h00 until very late.INKasi Xperience is proudly supported by KwaZulu-Natal Department of Community Safety & Liaison, eThekwini Municipality, Durban Tourism and SuperSpar.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjssp77zsW6KAVq8Vyb15zlM187EN4fuqNcDHuaDglajqMGPO9d7F3rJP0s-l-N2YcbliRqzSxdHBHsZRdv8AzFipFbZVY3ipLNClnR7kBtZJYTsCo5dlpwaxUGT_AN4NYrf0gj5gaNtyKB6ZaY0SZAERQk-N5b2WW4gFy3li8GiuSpFzemFn5M4_6KGaBRO9uPZIO3mCXmoYEbpEMTsHtDOHSWx53jhM96JUt8sjYUWBT1G3VbngJyDAadljbmmtDfGSTXQ0xwbAa1uTHrzS-ksP-bMb6LJ0wXpUXA\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzGNDbVrf9YQ6EAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
